                    <handDesc>
                       <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <seg type="script">Written in a mediocre handwriting</seg>
                                <date when="1536">16th century</date>
                                <desc>
                                   The handwriting retains some old palaeographical features: 
                                   መ, ቆ, ቶ, ዐ, የ, ደ, ጸ have angular shapes; 
                                   numerals are sometimes written without dashes; 
                                   ፲ is written with the loop and the linking line on the right side.
                          </desc>
                          <seg type="rubrication">
                             Nomina sacra, titles, Ethiopic numerals.
                          </seg>
                       </handNote>
                    </handDesc>
